==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''bonus'', '''good'''.

===Noun===
'''bonus'''  (''plural:'' '''[[bonuses]]''')
# Something extra that is good.
#:''The employee received a '''bonus''' for his excellent work.''

===Translations===
*Dutch: bonus
*Finnish: Bonus
*German: Bonus {{m}}
*Spanish: [[plus]] {{m}}, [[beneficio]] {{m}}
*Vietnamese: [[tiền thưởng]], [[tiền các]]

